Rustic cabin with LAKE VIEWS! Serene views of Mormon Lake can be seen from every bedroom, kitchen, porch, and the backyard! This recently REMODELED CABIN is nestled in the quiet neighborhood of Tall Pine Estates of Mormon Lake. Tasteful rustic decor has been added throughout the home including an abundance of upgrades and storage! An attached garage and three sheds provide plenty of room for storing toys, gear, and firewood for winter and summer activities. Featuring about 2200 sq ft with 3 bedrooms and 2 full baths, this home is large enough for family and friends to stay on weekends or reside year-round. A bonus loft brings additional light and space with vaulted ceilings perfect for entertaining! The home is energy efficient with TRIPLE-PANE windows and a wood burning stove to heat the home comfortably. HORSE PROPERTY! The backyard comes fully fenced including two additional pastures with multiple gates and vehicle ingress/egress points so bring your horses for horseback riding on the scenic trails within minutes of the home! With just over an acre of land the yard has a variety of established landscaping including berry bushes (blueberry and raspberry), three fruit trees (apple and peach) and ponderosa, spruce, and pinon pines. If you want to have a vegetable garden, an area with rich garden soil has been maintained with access to an inground freeze-proof garden hose bib. Upgrades to the cabin include: - New drywall, texture, and paint throughout the entire house (2025) - Custom wood trim and doors (2025) - Smart home-nest thermometer, sensors in bedrooms, and a Wi-Fi ceiling fan switch - Variable stage Trane furnace with electro air filtration - Dual water filtration system by waterdrop - Two carbon monoxide monitors, - Three custom mantles over the fireplace - Custom cedar rustic themed bathrooms (2025) - Installed Mueller Steel metal roof (2025) - Triple-pane gas filled windows (2019) - Replaced insulated automatic garage door (2024) - Upgraded electric tankless water heater supplies the whole house (2019) - Custom nature themed metal light switch plates - Updated plumbing with electric heat tape and replaced septic lines with easy access to tank clean-out (2023) - Wood fireplace stove insert (2018) - Metal loafing/woodshed (2020) - 10 by 16 lofted insulated Graceland Shed (2019) - 7 by 8 insulated Tuff Shed (2025) - Brick garden beds with bear & eagle chainsaw carved tree sculptures by local artist The community of Mormon Lake is close enough to the valley to enjoy a weekend getaway and only 30 minutes from Flagstaff for the amenities of shopping, restaurants, and skiing. The Mormon Lake Lodge is nearby with 24/7 gas & diesel pumps and a convenient store open during the day. The Lodge also has a seasonal steakhouse restaurant, pizza parlor and horseback trail rides operating during the summer months. The neighborhood is quiet and has an abundance of activities to enjoy such as fishing, hunting, hiking, stargazing, horseback riding, and wildlife sightings. Enjoy viewing herds of elk and deer from your own backyard along with NO HOA!
